    },
    {
      "id": "st2",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 39.09215241925091,
      "y": 454.21086638078026,
      "width": 924.2107424318606,
      "height": 325,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#000000",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1,
      "version": 906,
      "versionNonce": 466842433,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "text": "Prompt to generate invariants: “What must never happen—even during failure, retries, or scale?”\n\nExamples:\nDurable Acknowledgement: A request returns success only after its durable, authoritative state is persisted; after success, the state is\ndiscoverable despite single-node failure. Prevents: “acknowledged but lost” work, phantom runs, unreplayable actions.\n\nSingle Logical Identity via Idempotency: For a given tenant and idempotency key, there is exactly one logical entity; retries must never create\na second logical entity. Prevents: duplicate jobs/runs/orders/messages under retries and partitions.\n\nMonotonic State Machine: Entity state transitions are monotonic and terminal states are irreversible; the system never moves “backward” in\nthe lifecycle. Prevents: flapping state, double-execution, ambiguous recovery behavior.\n\nTenant Isolation: Tenant-scoped data, compute, and quotas never cross tenant boundaries; all execution and attribution is strictly tenant-\nscoped. Prevents: data leakage, noisy neighbor incidents, incorrect chargeback.\n\nFail-Closed Policy Enforcement (Auth/Budget/Quota): If policy cannot be evaluated (authz/budget/quota), the system fails closed: reject or\ndegrade, never silently oversubscribe. Prevents: runaway cost, privilege escalation, fairness violations during outages.\n\nExclusive Shared-Resource Writes with Fencing: Any mutation of a shared resource requires an exclusive lease and the latest fencing token\nfor that resource scope; stale tokens are rejected. Prevents: split-brain writers, zombie workers, corruption during failover.",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Prompt to generate invariants: “What must never happen—even during failure, retries, or scale?”\n\nExamples:\nDurable Acknowledgement: A request returns success only after its durable, authoritative state is persisted; after success, the state is discoverable despite single-node failure. Prevents: “acknowledged but lost” work, phantom runs, unreplayable actions.\n\nSingle Logical Identity via Idempotency: For a given tenant and idempotency key, there is exactly one logical entity; retries must never create a second logical entity. Prevents: duplicate jobs/runs/orders/messages under retries and partitions.\n\nMonotonic State Machine: Entity state transitions are monotonic and terminal states are irreversible; the system never moves “backward” in the lifecycle. Prevents: flapping state, double-execution, ambiguous recovery behavior.\n\nTenant Isolation: Tenant-scoped data, compute, and quotas never cross tenant boundaries; all execution and attribution is strictly tenant-scoped. Prevents: data leakage, noisy neighbor incidents, incorrect chargeback.\n\nFail-Closed Policy Enforcement (Auth/Budget/Quota): If policy cannot be evaluated (authz/budget/quota), the system fails closed: reject or degrade, never silently oversubscribe. Prevents: runaway cost, privilege escalation, fairness violations during outages.\n\nExclusive Shared-Resource Writes with Fencing: Any mutation of a shared resource requires an exclusive lease and the latest fencing token for that resource scope; stale tokens are rejected. Prevents: split-brain writers, zombie workers, corruption during failover.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "index": "aE",
      "frameId": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768939874842,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "autoResize": false
    },
