      "locked": false,
      "text": "Intent Level in a 45 minute interview: \nStep 2 (NFRs): acknowledge with 3–4 constraints\n    Example: At a high level, this needs high availability for Inferences,\nbounded latency, strict tenant isolation, and hard cost caps. I’ll call\nout where these shape the design as we go.\n\nStep 4 (APIs): acknowledge with 2 sentences (CP vs DP)\n    Example: I won’t enumerate every endpoint, but the API surface\nsplits cleanly into a control plane for specs, approvals, and status, and\na data plane for inference and health — all writes go through the\ncontrol plane.\n\nStep 5 (Data Model): acknowledge with ownership + mutability\n    Example: There’s an authoritative control-plane store for tenants,\nmodels, and rollouts, plus immutable audit and versioned artifacts; the\ndata plane only caches derived decisions and emits telemetry.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Intent Level in a 45 minute interview: \nStep 2 (NFRs): acknowledge with 3–4 constraints\n    Example: At a high level, this needs high availability for Inferences, bounded latency, strict tenant isolation, and hard cost caps. I’ll call out where these shape the design as we go.\n\nStep 4 (APIs): acknowledge with 2 sentences (CP vs DP)\n    Example: I won’t enumerate every endpoint, but the API surface splits cleanly into a control plane for specs, approvals, and status, and a data plane for inference and health — all writes go through the control plane.\n\nStep 5 (Data Model): acknowledge with ownership + mutability\n    Example: There’s an authoritative control-plane store for tenants, models, and rollouts, plus immutable audit and versioned artifacts; the data plane only caches derived decisions and emits telemetry.",
